ğŸš¦ Gateway Limits and Considerations
| Limit                        | Value               | Can Be Increased? |
| ---------------------------- | ------------------- | ----------------- |
| DX Connections per Region    | 50                  | âœ… Yes             |
| Virtual Interfaces per DX    | 50                  | âœ… Yes             |
| Max Bandwidth per Connection | 100 Gbps            | âŒ Fixed per port  |
| VGW per VPC                  | 1                   | âŒ No              |
| Transit VIFs                 | 1 per DX connection | âŒ No              |
ğŸ” High Availability â€“ Best Practices
| Design               | Best Practice                                            |
| -------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Redundancy**       | Use **2 DX connections** in **2 locations** for failover |
| **Backup**           | Use **VPN as a backup** to Direct Connect                |
| **Failover testing** | Regularly test failover paths                            |
| **Cross-region**     | Use **TGW** with **inter-region peering** if needed      |
ğŸ§  AWS recommends DX + VPN combo for hybrid enterprise workloads to ensure uptime and performance.

